       "id": "comp-2-2-e5",
       "type": "compose",
       "q": "Theme VII. Write a short story suggested by one of the following subjects: 1. The trout's revenge. 2. A sparrow's mistake. 3. A fortunate shot. 4. The freshman and the professor. 5. What the bookcase thought about it. (Correct with reference to meaning and clearness. Cross out unnecessary ands. Consider the beginnings of the sentences. Can you improve the euphony by a different choice of words?)",
       "model": "The trout's revenge. All summer the old trout had lain in the deep pool below the mill, and twice he had felt the bite of a hook and torn himself free. When the angler came again one bright morning and dropped his gaudy fly upon the water, the trout did not rise. He sank instead beneath a sunken log and waited, watching the fly drift past again and again. At last the man, growing careless, leaned far out over the bank to flick his line free of a branch; his foot slipped on the wet stone, and with a great splash he tumbled into the very pool he had fished so long. The trout, darting away unharmed, flicked his tail once at the dripping angler and slid back into the cool dark water.",
