       "q": "Theme XXI. Write a paragraph by furnishing specific instances for one of the following topic statements: 'It requires a man of courage and perseverance to become a pioneer'; 'Even so stupid a creature as a chicken may sometimes exhibit much intelligence'; 'Carelessness often leads into difficulty.' (Do your specific instances really illustrate the topic statement?)",
       "model": "Carelessness often leads into difficulty. A boy who leaves the garden gate open finds the cattle in the corn an hour later. A girl who forgets to wind the clock oversleeps and misses the only morning train. A man who does not look to his fire before bed may wake to find his barn in ashes. In each case a small neglect grew into a real misfortune.",
