       "type": "compose",
       "q": "Theme XLII. Write a paragraph telling why you believe one of the propositions in the preceding exercise: this city needs a new high school building; there should be a lunch room in this school; fairy stories should not be told to children.",
       "model": "There should be a lunch room in this school, because many pupils live too far away to go home at noon. Now those pupils eat cold food at their desks or buy poor meals at the corner store, and they come back to afternoon lessons tired and ill fed. A lunch room would give them a warm, wholesome meal under the school's own care, and a pupil who has eaten well works better through the afternoon. For these reasons I believe the school needs a lunch room.",
