       "id": "comp-4-4-e5",
       "type": "compose",
       "q": "Theme XLI. Write a paragraph, proving by one or more examples one of these propositions. (Do your examples really illustrate what you are trying to prove? Would your argument cause another to believe it?) Proposition: dogs are intelligent.",
       "model": "Dogs are intelligent, as many a familiar example shows. Our own collie learned in a single week to open the kitchen door by leaping at the latch, and afterward did it whenever he wished to come in. A shepherd's dog will gather a scattered flock at a low whistle, holding back the swift sheep and hurrying the slow ones with no further word from his master. Hunting dogs remember the ground they have covered and circle back to a bird they have once marked down. Such cases, which any one may match from his own knowledge, prove that the dog reasons about what he does and is far from a creature of blind habit.",
