       "type": "compose",
       "q": "Theme LXXIII: Write a story, using one of the plots you wrote for the preceding theme. (Are the events related in your story probable or improbable?)",
       "model": "The little clerk Henley found the wallet on the wet pavement outside the bank, fat with banknotes and bearing no name but a faded photograph. All the way home it burned in his pocket like a coal. He told himself the loser would never miss it, that his sick mother needed the doctor, that no one had seen him stoop. Yet he could not eat, and at midnight he was still turning the photograph over by the lamp. At the first gray light he dressed, walked back through the empty streets, and waited on the bank steps until the manager came; the face in the photograph was the manager's own little daughter. Henley handed it over without a word and turned to go, but the man called him back, and that was how the clerk got his first honest rise in the world.",
