       "model": "A real adventure that happened to me, such as 'The day I nearly drowned,' must be told in the first person, because only I witnessed my own fear and could honestly report it. A narrative such as 'How the firemen rescued the family' is better told in the third person, because no single person inside the story saw the whole rescue, and the teller must move among several actors to relate it.",
