       "model": "\"What!\" roared Mountain, leaping to his feet in a purple, swollen-veined fury. \"A reporter! In my own office!\"\n\"From the Banner, sir,\" said Dayton, not moving an inch. \"The public would like your own word on the Great Eastern and Western.\"\n\"My word!\" snapped the financier. \"My word is that you may go to the devil.\"\n\"That is one view,\" the reporter answered, drawing out his notebook. \"But a single honest sentence from you would be worth more than a column of guesses, and the guesses are already in print.\"\nMountain glared, breathing hard; then, to his own surprise, he laughed. \"Sit down,\" he growled. \"You have more nerve than my whole board of directors.\" And before the half hour was over, Dayton had his story.",
