       "id": "comp-9-5-e2",
       "type": "compose",
       "q": "Theme XCIII. Write an exposition that makes use of comparison. Suggested subjects: 1. A bad habit is a tyrant. 2. Typewritten letters. 3. The muskrat's house. 5. Methods of reading. 6. All the world's a stage. 7. Compare life to a flower.",
       "model": "A bad habit is a tyrant. Like a cruel ruler, it first wins entry by small favors and easy pleasures, then slowly demands more until it governs the whole household of a man's life. He believes he is free to throw it off whenever he likes, but the tyrant has quietly disarmed him; each day's obedience makes the next refusal harder. In the end the subject obeys not because he wishes to, but because he has forgotten how to command himself.",
