       "id": "comp-9-5-e3",
       "type": "compose",
       "q": "Following Burke's method of obverse statement, explain an idea by first ruling out the related ideas with which it might be confused, then naming the one you mean. (Brooks's model: 'The proposition is peace. Not peace through the medium of war; not peace to be hunted through the labyrinth of intricate and endless negotiations...')",
       "model": "What I ask for is freedom. Not the freedom that means doing whatever one pleases without thought of others; not the freedom that is only license, throwing off all law and restraint; not the freedom that the strong seize at the cost of the weak. It is simple freedom: the liberty of a man to govern his own life and conscience within just laws that protect the same liberty in his neighbor. By excluding these false kinds of freedom, the true kind stands out the more clearly.",
